Source: isdnutils
Section: net
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Paul Slootman <paul@debian.org>
Standards-Version: 2.5.0

Package: isdnutils
Architecture: alpha i386 sparc
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: basic ISDN utilities
 This package includes the basic utilities to get an ISDN system up and
 running.
 It does NOT include all logging and monitoring utilities (it includes
 imon and imontty only), nor the `vbox' answering machine program.

Package: isdnextra
Architecture: alpha i386 sparc
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: various ISDN logging and monitoring utilities
 This package adds to the basic ISDN utilities the other, enhanced, logging
 and monitoring utilities.  You want this if e.g. you want a record of in and
 outgoing calls or various X window utilities.

Package: isdnvbox
Architecture: alpha i386 sparc
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: ISDN "voice box" answering machine
 If you want to use your Linux system as a digital answering machine, choose
 this package. You can let the system answer more than one number, give
 different messages to different callers, have recorded messages emailed to
 you, and much more. It's a very flexible package.

Package: isdnutils-doc
Section: doc
Architecture: all
Description: documentation for all ISDN-related packages
 The other ISDN-related packages only include basic documentation (e.g.
 manpages); this package supplies more detailed information.
